<p><b>Cryptomnesia</b>, or inadvertent plagiarism, is a <a href="/wiki/Memory_bias" title="Memory bias" class="mw-redirect">memory bias</a> whereby a person falsely recalls generating a thought, an idea, a song, or a joke, when the thought was actually generated by someone else<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup>. In these cases, the person is not deliberately engaging in <a href="/wiki/Plagiarism" title="Plagiarism">plagiarism</a>, but is rather experiencing a memory as if it were a new inspiration.</p>
